4,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d191908-Reviews-or0-Ibis_London_Greenwich-London_England.html#REVIEWS,Ibis London Greenwich Hotel Reviews,Excellent budget break,"First stay outside home since lockdown in March. Any slight anxiety soon resolved by the friendly welcome from reception and the sight of our clean and quiet room. Hand sanitiser points by the entrance and the lift; face coverings requested in public areas. Our room was described as 'overlooking a courtyard' which turned out to be several air-conditioner outlets and a brick wall! However there are plenty of superb views elsewhere in Greenwich so we were happy to trade  beauty for quietness. Facilities in the room are on the minimal side: wall-mounted soap dispensers and cramped toilet; kettle but no crockery (although this is a temporary anti-Covid measure and paper cups are available from reception). The bed was very comfortable. For the price (a bargain for London) we were very happy. The only minor niggle was the carpet which was stained and 'tired'. We did not have breakfast (we were offered a package of cereal and croissants before 09.00 or the option of a cooked breakfast in Caf√© Rouge afterwards) because we preferred to find our own locally: there are plenty of other caf√©s and restaurants within five minutes' walk. The location is ideal: just off the major road into the town centre and five minutes from the mainline station, midway between two DLR stations and near plenty of buses (and the riverboat pier). The town centre, Greenwich Market and the Old Naval College complex are gems which are probably best seen now when many tourists are staying away.‚Ä¶",Date of stay: September 2020,4.0
